</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="19" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="19">The male genitalia of the unique type could not be found. Therefore the pygofer (originally not figured) could not be examined and compared to the new species. Also, the original figure of the aedeagus (shown here, Fig. 10) did not show the membranous area of the basal apodeme shown in our new species. We conclude that this area was probably overlooked and add a line to the figure to show its approximate position.</paragraph>
